  "title": "Lane cake",
  "subtitle": "Southern American white layer cake with bourbon raisin filling",
  "excerpt": "Lane cake is an Alabama layer cake from the 1890s: white sponge layers filled with a cooked custard of egg yolks, butter, sugar, pecans, raisins, and bourbon whiskey. The filling is rich and fudge-like once cooled, and the cake is finished with a fluffy seven-minute frosting. It is a celebration cake and keeps well for several days. The bourbon quantity is generous; the filling should taste unmistakably of it.",
