    {
      "slug": "seven-minute-frosting",
      "term": "Seven-minute frosting",
      "definition": "An American cooked meringue frosting made by whisking egg whites, sugar, cream of tartar, and water over a double boiler for seven minutes until thick, glossy, and marshmallow-like. The heat cooks the egg whites and dissolves the sugar simultaneously. The frosting sets firm on the outside and stays soft inside. It must be used within a few hours of making; it does not store well."
    }
